    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-24T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4083a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-24T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1185. In view of need for preparation in the event Navy will be in a position to
                    transport second group of Poles from India, will you <pb facs="0341" n="331"
                        xml:id="pg_331"/> kindly advise us when it will be possible to arrange for
                    reception of such a group.</p>
                <p>We have no definite information about transportation, but there is possibility an
                    arrangement can be made similar to one just completed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
